# Normalize line endings: keep text files as LF in the repo regardless of
# the contributor's platform. Prevents phantom whole-file conflicts when
# Windows checkouts re-introduce CRLF.
* text=auto eol=lf

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Auto-generated files — DO NOT line-merge.
#
# Git's default three-way merge on these produces either garbled output
# (lockfiles) or syntactically-broken JSON (the drizzle journal). Marking
# them `-diff merge=binary` makes Git treat each side as opaque, so a
# conflict surfaces as a single "pick one side" decision instead of
# hundreds of inline `<<<<<<<` hunks. This is also what GitHub's
# server-side merge sees — keep these `binary` so a conflict blocks the
# merge button rather than risking a corrupt auto-merge landing on main.
#
# pnpm-lock.yaml: `scripts/install-hooks.sh` installs a LOCAL-ONLY merge
# driver (registered in .git/info/attributes, which overrides this file
# for your clone only) so local merges/rebases auto-resolve the lockfile
# and re-run `pnpm install`. If you ever resolve one by hand:
#
#   git checkout --theirs pnpm-lock.yaml    # or --ours, whichever is closer
#   pnpm install                            # regenerates from package.json
#   git add pnpm-lock.yaml
#
# _journal.json: DO NOT hand-edit or splice it. It is frozen at 52 entries
# and new migrations are no longer journaled; rebuilding it can make
# migrate.mjs re-apply or skip migrations against production (see
# docs/migration-state-investigation-2026-05-08.md). The marker below is
# only a guard — if it ever conflicts, take either side verbatim.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

pnpm-lock.yaml                                  -diff merge=binary
lib/resupply-db/drizzle/meta/_journal.json      -diff merge=binary

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Binary assets — never diff, never line-merge.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

*.png       binary
*.jpg       binary
*.jpeg      binary
*.gif       binary
*.ico       binary
*.webp      binary
*.pdf       binary
*.woff      binary
*.woff2     binary
*.ttf       binary
*.otf       binary
*.eot       binary
*.mp4       binary
*.webm      binary
*.mov       binary
*.zip       binary
*.gz        binary
*.tgz       binary
